                <br><br><strong>Merchandise Information and Pricing</strong><br>

                The purpose of this policy is to establish guidelines and procedures for making changes to product information and pricing in the store. This policy aims to ensure accuracy, consistency, and transparency in communicating product details and prices to our customers, suppliers, and internal stakeholders.
                This policy applies to all employees, managers, and stakeholders involved in the process of updating, maintaining, and communicating product information and pricing in the store.
                The Product Management team is responsible for overseeing and managing all product-related information. They shall collaborate with relevant departments to ensure that product details, specifications, descriptions, and images are accurate and up to date.
                Any changes to product information are documented and submitted to the Product Management team for review and approval. The team will assess the proposed changes for accuracy, compliance, and alignment with the store's overall product strategy.
                Once the product information changes are approved, the Product Management team will communicate the updates to all relevant departments, including Sales, Marketing, Customer Support, and Website Management. This communication should be timely and comprehensive to ensure consistency across all channels.
                A Pricing Committee shall be established, consisting of representatives from Finance, Sales, Marketing, and Product Management. The committee will be responsible for reviewing and approving any changes to product pricing.
                <br><br><strong>Factors Considered for Pricing Changes</strong><br>
                The Pricing Committee shall consider various factors before approving pricing changes, including but not limited to:
                <br> Cost of production
                <br> Market demand and competition
                <br> Currency fluctuations (for international sales)
                <br> Seasonal or promotional pricing strategies
                <br> Profit margins and financial goals

                <br><br><strong>The Pricing Committee will follow a structured process for pricing changes:</strong><br>
                <br> Initiation: A pricing change proposal is submitted to the Pricing Committee by the Product Management team.
                <br> Analysis: The committee evaluates the proposal based on the factors mentioned above
                <br> Approval: If the proposal aligns with the company's pricing strategy and financial objectives, it is approved by the Pricing Committee.
                <br> Communication: The approved pricing changes are communicated to the Sales team, Website Management, and other relevant stakeholders for implementation.
                <br><br>
                Special offers, discounts, and promotions shall be managed by the Marketing and Sales teams in alignment with the pricing strategy and overall marketing plan. The Pricing Committee may be involved in evaluating the potential impact of significant promotions on the company's financials.
                All product information and pricing changes must comply with local laws and regulations, as well as any industry-specific standards or guidelines.
                This policy shall be regularly reviewed and updated by the Product Management team in collaboration with relevant stakeholders to ensure its effectiveness and relevance.
